 Willowvale - Willowvale police have appealed to the public to assist them in solving a case of a missing 41-year-old woman, Nonkululeko Mvandaba, from Mvandaba Locality, Mboya Village at Willowvale. "It is alleged she was last seen when she left Willowvale on Thursday, 04 June 2020 at about 12:00 to fetch a bakkie in East London," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "Her husband last spoke to her telephonically on 04 June at about 16:00, by that time, she had already crossed the Kei Bridge. "The husband has been calling her on her cellphone, without success." Captain Manatha said that the missing person is light in complexion, 1,8m tall and she has natural grey hair. "Anyone who can assist Willowvale Police to locate the missing person is kindly requested to contact Willowvale Police at 047 499 6234 or Crime Stop 08600 10111," he added. "All correspondence will be treated confidentially." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  